'''Ratanang Nke''' (born 2 October 1975, Rustenburg) is chairman of Luka Business Forum Investment Trust, LexTalio Forensic Professionals (Pty) Ltd and [[Platinum Stars F.C.]]

==Career==

Nke held positions in the public sector such as Public Prosecutor, Control Prosecutor and State Advocate<ref>{{cite web|title=Ratanang Nke|url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/ratanangnke|website=LinkedIn|accessdate=25 September 2014}}</ref> focused on combating economic crimes. He also held positions in the private sector such as CEO, Director and Managing Director of various Forensic & Investigative accounting service companies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ratanang Nke|url=http://whoswho.co.za/ratanang-nke-8909|website=Who's Who|accessdate=25 September 2014}}</ref> In 2010, Nke compiled the "Nke Report" on former Ekurhuleni Metro police chief and current head of the Independent Police Investigative Directorate, [[Robert McBride (police officer)|Robert McBride]] who was charged with drunk driving, fraud and defeating the ends of justice.<ref>{{cite web|title=Report links McBride to alleged corrupt deals|url=http://www.iol.co.za/news/south-africa/report-links-mcbride-to-alleged-corrupt-deals-1.670471|website=IOL News|accessdate=25 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Report links McBride to alleged corrupt deals Report fingers McBride; Wheeling and dealing faces further scrutiny.(News)|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-232386012.html|accessdate=25 September 2014|agency=highbeam.com|date=July 22, 2010}}</ref>

Outside of the legal arena Nke founded the Ratanang Nke Foundation for Hope which focuses at education, sports development and various philanthropic endeavors. Nke is also actively involved in management of [[Platinum Stars F.C.]] as well as in the management of its parent company the Royal Bafokeng Sports (Pty) Ltd<ref>{{cite web|title=Platinum Stars chairman Ratanang Nke has dismissed claims the Premier Soccer League club may be sold|url=https://za.news.yahoo.com/nke-dikwena-not-sale-124131417.html|website=Yahoo South Africa News|accessdate=25 September 2014}}</ref>

